Today's the day. The new Premier League season kicks off tonight with Arsenal taking on Crystal Palace at Selhurst Park, but there is still just under a month of the summer transfer window to play out. Plenty of dealings are still to be done before the September 1 deadline, with Manchester United, Chelsea, Tottenham Hotspur, and more eyeing more reinforcements. Chelsea look set to announce the signing of Marc Cucurella from Brighton & Hove Albion after agreeing a deal worth in excess of £60million for the Spanish defender. His impending arrival has prompted Thomas Tuchel to hold crunch talks with Ben Chilwell. United are still eagerly awaiting a positive outcome from their Frenkie de Jong saga, with his future still up in the air due to deferred wage payments owed by Barcelona. Meanwhile, the Red Devils hunt attacking firepower after Anthony Martial's latest ill-timed injury. Tottenham are closing in on their seventh signing of Antonio Conte's first summer as head coach, but fans may not be too happy with the structure of the deal... Express Sport keeps you up to date on all the latest transfer news coming out of the Premier League and across Europe below... JUST IN: Ronaldo's behaviour in Man Utd training is absolutely typical